The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 2: The countrys forex reserves declined $144 million to $283.49 billion in the week ended December 25 from $283.64 billion in the previous week, the Reserve Bank of India said in its weekly report. During the period, foreign currency assets dipped to $258.71 billion, down $132 million, from $258.85 billion in the previous week, the RBI said.                            
	 Milan, Jan. 2: Italian confectioner Ferrero has met private equity firms as well as Hershey Co to discuss a possible bid for Britains Cadbury Plc, Il Sole 24 Ore daily reported on Saturday. The coming weeks will determine whether the family-held company will make an offer for the British confectionery maker, rivalling a hostile 10-billion ($15.9 billion) bid from Kraft Foods Inc.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 2: The State Bank of India today revised its interest rates on foreign currency non-resident (B) account deposits and non-resident external term deposits with immediate effect. With this, FCNR(B) deposits in dollar, having a maturity of 1-2 years, will attract an interest of 1.98 per cent against 2.02 per cent earlier.                            
	 Calcutta, Jan. 2: Boston-based private equity firm Bain Capital has acquired a 15.39 per cent stake in city-based Himadri Chemicals amp; Industries for Rs 252 crore.                                                                                                                          
